wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant-Colonel William Douglas Stock Sanday,  (born 1883) was a British World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories.

response: On 6 September 1916, Rosencrantz and Fahlbusch engaged Sopwith 1 1/2 Strutter two-seater fighters from No. 70 Squadron RFC. The German duo were shot down in flames over Malincourt, France. Credit for their demise was given to Bernard Paul Gascoigne Beanlands, William Sanday, and their observers.
* William Sanday (theologian) (1843–1920), British theologian and biblical scholar
* William Sanday (RAF officer) (1883–?), British World War I flying ace
